Originally W. Richard Stevens (UNIX Network Programming, 2nd Edition, Vol-1)

Heavily modified by Ayub <mrayub@gmail.com>
This version handles timeouts.

Default INTERVAL=1, TIMEOUT=3
You can set INTERVAL and TIMEOUT (both in seconds) in the gcc command line.
gcc -o myping4 myping4.c -DINTERVAL=2 -DTIMEOUT=5
